"title": "8840: unfaithfulness, to God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8840: unfaithfulness, to god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the OT the terms of the covenant with God were constantly broken by Israel by acts of idolatry and disobedience. The consequence was God's judgment, which eventually included exile.</p>\n<h2>Warnings within the covenant</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:8\">NEH 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:1\">LEV 26:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:14-Lev26:17\">LEV 26:14–26:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:31-Lev26:33\">LEV 26:31–26:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:25-Deut4:27\">DEU 4:25–4:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:19-Deut8:20\">DEU 8:19–8:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:22\">PRO 2:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:13\">EZK 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek15:8\">EZK 15:8</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness seen in idolatry</h2>\n<h3>Idolatry as marital unfaithfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:20\">JER 3:20</a></strong> <em>The covenant between God and Israel at Sinai viewed in terms of a marriage contract</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:6-Jer3:9\">JER 3:6–3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12-Jer3:14\">JER 3:12–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:2\">JER 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2\">HOS 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry as prostitution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:25\">1CH 5:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:10-Hos4:12\">HOS 4:10–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:1\">HOS 9:1</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry as abandoning God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:16\">JER 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:13\">JDG 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:19\">JER 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:6\">JER 15:6</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness seen in other forms of disobedience</h2>\n<h3>Trust in money and possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:24-Job31:28\">JOB 31:24–31:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:4\">JER 49:4</a></p>\n<h3>Doing wrong to others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:5-Num5:6\">NUM 5:5–5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:2\">LEV 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:3\">PRO 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:2\">PRO 13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:21-Isa1:23\">ISA 1:21–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:6-Hos6:7\">HOS 6:6–6:7</a></p>\n<h3>Marrying foreign wives</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:2\">EZR 10:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:1-Ezra9:4\">EZR 9:1–9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:27\">NEH 13:27</a></p>\n<h3>Withholding tithes and offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1\">JOS 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:20\">JOS 22:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8\">MAL 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Breaches in the ritual law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:33\">1SA 14:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:7-Mal1:8\">MAL 1:7–1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness as a characteristic of God's people throughout the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:11\">JER 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:37-Acts7:41\">ACT 7:37–7:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16-Judg2:17\">JDG 2:16–2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:7-Hag1:9\">HAG 1:7–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness among Israel's leadership</h2>\n<h3>The unfaithfulness of the priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:1-Ezra9:2\">EZR 9:1–9:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:14\">2CH 36:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:7-Mal2:8\">MAL 2:7–2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Unfaithful kings</h3>\n<p>Solomon's unfaithfulness leads to unfaithfulness among his subjects:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:4-1Kgs11:5\">1KI 11:4–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:33\">1KI 11:33</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:1-2Chr12:2\">2CH 12:1–12:2</a> <em>Rehoboam</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16-2Chr26:18\">2CH 26:16–26:18</a> <em>Uzziah's bad example</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:19-2Chr28:23\">2CH 28:19–28:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:19\">2CH 29:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:9\">2KI 21:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:9\">2CH 33:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:16\">2KI 21:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:19\">2CH 33:19</a></p>\n<h2>Unfaithfulness leads to judgment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:20\">DEU 32:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:27\">PSA 73:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:56-Ps78:59\">PSA 78:56–78:59</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:18\">PRO 21:18</a></p>\n<h3>Individuals judged for unfaithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1\">JOS 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:25\">JOS 7:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:13\">1CH 10:13</a></p>\n<h3>Wandering in the desert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:33\">NUM 14:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:34-Num14:35\">NUM 14:34–14:35</a></p>\n<h3>The people taken into exile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23\">EZK 39:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:1\">1CH 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:7\">DAN 9:7</a></p>\n<h2>Restoration following repentance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:25-Ezek39:26\">EZK 39:25–39:26</a></strong> <em>God's purpose through the exile is to bring about the eventual repentance and restoration of his people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:40-Lev26:42\">LEV 26:40–26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:1-Deut30:3\">DEU 30:1–30:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:8-Neh1:9\">NEH 1:8–1:9</a></p>",
